main event: Civilians reported seeing two objects in the sky over Brooklyn, New York on September 30, 1956, but insufficient data indicates they were likely aircraft.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 1 minute,The observer described one object larger than the size of Mars and another the size of a pinhead,One object was bluish white and the other was yellowish white,The first sighting was heading SW, followed by a NE trajectory for the second sighting,The report concludes there was insufficient data to classify the objects definitively.
